%N A380650 The largest number which is a linear combination of the divisors of n with nonnegative integer coefficients such that no linear combination with smaller nonnegative integer coefficients is equal to n.
%C A380650 The mean of this sequence and Euler's totient function A000010 is approximately (but not exactly) equal to n.
%C A380650 The definition has evolved from a recreational question asked by P. M. Higgins, asking what maximal sum of money can be produced using British coins so no sum of one pound is produced by any subset of these coins.
%F A380650 a(n) = (A145388(n) - 1)/2. - _Hugo Pfoertner_, Jan 29 2025
%e A380650 For n = 12, the largest sum is 17 = 0*1 + 0*2 + 1*3 + 2*4 + 1*6 = 0*1 + 0*2 + 3*3 + 2*4 + 0*6.
%e A380650 For n = 30, the largest sum is 60 = 1*1 + 0*2 + 0*3 + 0*5 + 4*6 + 2*10 + 1*15.
%o A380650 (Python)
